Citation.sAbstract: Solubility data were determined for the first time for p-tolylboronic acid, bromobenzene, and 4-phenyltoluene in carbon dioxide at (353 and 383) K and between pressures of (98 and 317) bar. Data were obtained using a cloud point apparatus fitted with an internal stirrer. The results were correlated using Chrastil's density based model.
Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of p-Tolylboronic Acid, Bromobenzene and 4-Phenyltoluene in Carbon Dioxide at Elevated Pressures
sAuthor: Kee, C. K. Y.[Connie K. Y.]
